      • get

        public java.lang.Double get(UserRequest uRequest)
        Gets the Cost associated with a UserRequest, if it exists, and places the Request at the beginning of the cache.
        Returns:
        The Cost associated with a UserRequest, or null if it does not exist.

      • getEstimatedCost

        public double getEstimatedCost(UserRequest uRequest)
        Gets the estimated Cost of a UserRequest. If the Request exists in the cache, it will return its Cost. Otherwise, it will find the most similar UserRequest in the cache.
        Returns:
        The estimated Cost of the Incoming Request.

      • put

        public void put(UserRequest uRequest,
       double cost)
        Puts a UserRequest and its Cost in the cache, if it is not present. If the cache has reached its limit, it removes the oldest member (LRU Policy).

      • putAll

        public void putAll(java.util.Map<UserRequest,java.lang.Double> uRequestsCosts)
        Puts all UserRequests and their Costs at the end of the cache.
